President of the United States Barack Obama awards a Medal of Honor posthumously to Robert James Miller of the US Army Green Berets for "conspicuous gallantry ... at risk of life above and beyond the call of duty" while fighting in the War in Afghanistan on January 25, 2008. (CNN)At least 16 people, including the governor of Kunduz province, Mohammad Omar, are killed in a bombing. (Al Jazeera) (Voice of America)